menu "breadboard: bb_task_registry"

config BB_TASK_REGISTRY_MAX
    int "Task registry capacity (max concurrently-tracked FreeRTOS tasks)"
    default 24
    range 1 64
    help
        Capacity of the diagnostic task registry consumed by
        GET /api/diag/tasks and the "rtos" bb_pub telemetry source. Every
        self-registering task-creation site registers here (best-effort); a
        full registry logs a warning and does NOT fail task creation. Must be
        <= BB_REGISTRY_SNAPSHOT_MAX (64).

config BB_TASK_REGISTRY_WDT_SUPPORT
    bool "Route per-task hardware Task WDT subscribe/feed through bb_task_registry"
    default y
    depends on ESP_TASK_WDT_EN
    help
        When enabled, bb_task_registry_register()'s opts->hw_wdt_subscribe
        performs esp_task_wdt_add(handle) on the caller's behalf, and
        bb_task_registry_deregister() performs the matching
        esp_task_wdt_delete(handle). When disabled (or the Task WDT itself
        is off), hw_wdt_subscribe is accepted but is a no-op — registration
        always succeeds.

endmenu
